   4class PhonemeClass(Entity):
   5    prefix = "phon"
   6
   7    @profile
   8    def __init__(self, txt, **kwargs):
   9        super().__init__(txt, **kwargs)
  10
  11    @cached_property
  12    def is_vowel(self):
  13        if not hasattr(self, "cons") or self.cons is None:
  14            return None
  15        if self.cons > 0:
  16            return False
  17        if self.cons < 1:
  18            return True
  19        return None
  20
  21    def to_json(self):
  22        resd = super().to_json()
  23        resd["_class"] = "Phoneme"
  24        resd.pop("children")
  25        return resd
  26
  27    @property
  28    def is_onset(self):
  29        return self._attrs.get("is_onset")
  30
  31    @property
  32    def is_rime(self):
  33        return self._attrs.get("is_rime")
  34
  35    @property
  36    def is_nucleus(self):
  37        return self._attrs.get("is_nucleus")
  38
  39    @property
  40    def is_coda(self):
  41        return self._attrs.get("is_coda")

  44@cache
  45@profile
  46def get_phoneme_featuretable():
  47    ft = panphon.FeatureTable()
  48    return ft
  49
  50
  51# @cache
  52@profile
  53def Phoneme(txt, **kwargs):
  54    phon = txt
  55    ft = get_phoneme_featuretable()
  56    phonl = ft.word_fts(phon)
  57    if not phonl:
  58        # logger.error(f'What is this phoneme? {phon}')
  59        if phon in get_ipa_info():
  60            phond = get_ipa_info().get(phon, {})
  61        else:
  62            # logger.error(f"What is this phoneme? No features found for it: {phon}")
  63            phond = {}
  64    else:
  65        phond = phonl[0].data
  66    phonobj = PhonemeClass(phon, **phond)
  67    return phonobj

Root Entity class representing a hierarchical structure in prosodic analysis.

This class serves as the base for various prosodic entities such as texts, stanzas, lines, words, syllables, and phonemes. It provides common functionality for managing hierarchical relationships, attributes, and data representation.

Attributes:
  • child_type (str): The type of child entities this entity can contain.
  • is_parseable (bool): Whether this entity can be parsed.
  • index_name (str): The name used for indexing this entity type.
  • prefix (str): A prefix used for attribute naming.
  • list_type (type): The type of list used for storing children.
  • cached_properties_to_clear (list): Properties to clear from cache.
  • use_cache (bool): Whether to use caching for this entity.
  • sep (str): Separator used when joining child texts.
